==Trivia==
*In the comics, Black Panther was a member of the [[Avengers]] and the [[Illuminati]], a group made of the smartest and most powerful characters in the Marvel Universe (with him being the eighth smartest man in the world) including [[Black Bolt]], [[Tony Stark]], [[Bruce Banner]], [[Medusa]], [[Hank Pym]], and [[Stephen Strange]]. In [[w:c:marvel:Black Panther Vol 7 3|Black Panther Vol 7 #3]], it is revealed that "T'Challa" translates to "he who put the knife where it belonged." He also got married to [[Storm|Ororo Munroe/Storm]].
**The MCU later offered a different translation of the name "T'Challa" with the birth of his son, [[T'Challa II]]; who bears his name. While living in Haiti, the junior T'Challa was raised under the name "Toussaint," said to the French Haitian translation of his Wakandan name. Thus; T'Challa's name indirectly translates to "All Saints."

==Behind the Scenes==
*Black Panther was the first of the Marvel characters whose movie rights reverted to Marvel, having been previously owned by {{WPS|Artisan Entertainment}}, {{WPS|Columbia Pictures}}, and 20th Century Fox. [[Marvel Studios]] got the rights back in 2005.
**The character almost had a film in the 90's starring [[Wesley Snipes]].
**The character would have been in the third or fourth [[Fantastic Four]] film directed by {{WPS|Tim Story}}, and was considered to be played by [[Djimon Hounsou]].
*The late [[Michael Kenneth Williams]] expressed interest in portraying Black Panther before [[Chadwick Boseman]] was cast.<ref>[http://www.cinemablend.com/new/One-Hollywood-Best-Actors-Campaigning-Play-Black-Panther-67324.html One Of Hollywood's Best Actors Is Campaigning To Play Black Panther]</ref>
*{{WPS|Chad L. Coleman}}, {{WPS|John Boyega}}, {{WPS|Noel Clarke}}, [[Anthony Mackie]], [[Djimon Hounsou]], [[Chiwetel Ejiofor]] and [[Adewale Akinnuoye-Agbaje]] were also considered to play Black Panther. Mackie, Hounsou, Ejiofor and Agbaje would go on to play [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]], [[Korath]], [[Baron Mordo]] and [[Kurse]] respectively.
*According to [[Kevin Feige]], the Black Panther was included in ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'' as a third party, someone with a different point of view from both [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and [[Iron Man]].
*[[Jason Chu]], [[Gui DaSilva-Greene]], [[Aaron Toney]], [[Daniel Graham]], [[Nico Woulard]], [[Kofi Yiadom]], [[Anis Cheurfa]], [[Troy Butler]] and [[Khalil' La'Marr Pickett]] were stunt doubles for [[Chadwick Boseman]] in the role of Black Panther.
*[[Qualen Bradley]] was a stand-in for [[Chadwick Boseman]] in the role of Black Panther.
*Black Panther, [[Black Widow]], and [[Spider-Man]] are the only characters in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] to receive a solo movie following their debut.

